Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Line a small shallow baking pan with heavy foil. Spray with cooking oil spray. Place chicken breasts on work surface, cover with plastic wrap, and pound lightly. Place breasts on pan. In a small bowl, stir together salad dressing and taco seasoning. Spread over top of chicken. Sprinkle crushed tortilla chips over chicken, pressing into the chicken lightly. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until cooked through. Spoon salsa over the top. Serve with additional salsa.